data.title: Do the people of Taiwan call themselves Taiwanese or Chinese?
data.meta_description:
Answer (1 of 14): Generally, both.

This is due to a nuisance of Chinese language which is not captured in Chinese.

There are two terms in Chinese, Huaren 华人 and Zhongguoren 中国人, wich both are translated as “Chinese”.
